from Mr. Trump's national
security team yesterday.

18:37.867 --> 18:41.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And in a tweet this morning,
the president wrote: "Iran has
been formally put on notice

18:42.567 --> 18:45.067 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
for firing a ballistic missile."

18:45.067 --> 18:50.067 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's not clear just what "on
notice" means, but Mr. Trump
was asked today whether military

18:50.867 --> 18:52.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
action is off the table.

18:52.900 --> 18:54.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP, President
of the United States:
Nothing is off the table.

18:54.933 --> 18:59.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: A top adviser to
Iran's supreme leader, Ayatollah
Khamenei, dismissed it all

19:01.733 --> 19:05.467 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
today, saying: "The American
government will understand that
threatening Iran is useless."

19:07.533 --> 19:11.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
By contrast, the administration
has been relatively quiet about
new fighting in Eastern Ukraine

19:13.233 --> 19:18.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
between government forces and
Russian-backed rebels, though,
late today, the U.S. ambassador

19:20.267 --> 19:23.967 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to the U.N., Nikki Haley, said
the situation requires clear
and wrong strong condemnation

19:25.333 --> 19:27.467 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of Russian actions.

19:27.467 --> 19:32.467 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Mr. Trump's conciliatory talk
about Russia and his critiques
of the European Union have

19:33.567 --> 19:36.667 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
leaders on the
continent concerned.

19:36.667 --> 19:38.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Donald Tusk is president
of the European Council.

19:38.733 --> 19:43.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DONALD TUSK, European Council
President: We should today
remind our American friends of

19:45.200 --> 19:48.833 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
their own motto:
United we stand.

19:48.833 --> 19:51.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Divided, we fall.

19:51.433 --> 19:55.167 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Meanwhile,
a phone call Saturday
with Australia's Prime
Minister Malcolm Turnbull

19:56.367 --> 19:58.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
is raising eyebrows.

19:58.500 --> 20:03.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Washington Post reports
the president told Turnbull,
"This was the worst call by

20:04.233 --> 20:06.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
