40:37.333 --> 40:39.933 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
high school.

40:39.933 --> 40:44.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Most of the girls come
from large families
and would normally be
selling food and water

40:44.200 --> 40:47.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
in the streets, or
something worse.

40:47.500 --> 40:51.767 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Meyler says the extreme
poverty in Liberia
leads to particularly
insidious behaviors.

40:51.767 --> 40:56.767 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
KATIE MEYLER: How bad
when you're trying just
every single day to get
a cup of rice to stay

40:57.467 --> 40:59.600 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
alive?

40:59.600 --> 41:02.767 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You know, I've seen and heard
and know of mothers that have
ended up prostituting their

41:02.767 --> 41:07.767 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
own children just to survive,
and it sounds horrific to
anybody on the outside.

41:08.833 --> 41:09.867 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Of course.

41:09.867 --> 41:11.333 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
How can a mother do that?

41:11.333 --> 41:13.367 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But how could a mother
let her daughter die, too?

41:13.367 --> 41:18.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Meyler's
passion for social justice began
more than 20 years ago as a

41:18.233 --> 41:22.667 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
teenager in suburban New
Jersey, where she was
raised by a single mother.

41:22.667 --> 41:25.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Often, the family was
dysfunctional, she says.

41:25.133 --> 41:27.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Often, they had
to go on welfare.

41:27.833 --> 41:29.867 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Meyler says she found
solace at her church.

41:29.867 --> 41:34.467 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KATIE MEYLER: It felt good
to help others, and it helped
me get out of my own things

41:34.467 --> 41:35.967 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
that were going on in my life.

41:35.967 --> 41:39.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, I got addicted to really
making other people happy.

41:39.133 --> 41:43.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: She went
on to graduate from college,
the first in her family to do

41:43.033 --> 41:48.033 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
so, and took a paid
internship with the charity
Samaritan's Purse, which
assigned her to Liberia.

41:50.033 --> 41:52.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KATIE MEYLER: I didn't
know where Liberia was on
a map, and I Googled it.

41:52.433 --> 41:54.167 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: So it was
meant to be for six months?

41:54.167 --> 41:55.467 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
KATIE MEYLER: Yes.

41:55.467 --> 41:56.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO:
It's been 11 years.

41:56.333 --> 41:57.533 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

41:57.533 --> 41:59.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO:
What happened?

41:59.600 --> 42:02.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KATIE MEYLER: There's a saying
that nobody chooses Liberia,
that Liberia chooses you.

42:02.433 --> 42:07.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think part of it is, you come
here and you see the amount
of need the place has, and

42:09.567 --> 42:13.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the people are very warm
and open, and you can make
a big difference here.

42:13.900 --> 42:16.400 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: She
saw a need for education.

42:16.400 --> 42:21.267 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Ten years ago, more
than half of all primary
school-aged children
didn't attend, collateral

42:22.700 --> 42:25.500 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
damage from this country's
14-year-long civil war.

42:25.500 --> 42:30.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, Meyler began raising
money, at first mostly through
her church for scholarships.

42:32.100 --> 42:34.067 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
But she quickly became
disenchanted with
the existing schools.

42:34.067 --> 42:38.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KATIE MEYLER: They're not really
learning anything at school,
because the teachers don't

42:38.033 --> 42:40.033 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
come on time.

42:40.033 --> 42:44.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Even -- both in public and
private schools, it's very rare
that teachers show up and they

42:45.200 --> 42:47.167 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
are accountable.

42:47.167 --> 42:50.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Meyler
decided she had to start her
own school, so she raised money

42:50.000 --> 42:55.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
from both small and large donors
in the United States, purchased
a building, and hired teachers.

42:57.367 --> 43:01.767 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The school provides breakfast
and lunch, medical services,
and after-school programs.

43:01.767 --> 43:06.767 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There's a strong emphasis
on empowering girls to stand
up against sexual abuse.

43:08.033 --> 43:09.300 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The school can
accommodate 180 students.

43:09.300 --> 43:13.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Hundreds more wish
they could attend.

43:15.267 --> 43:17.767 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
We met one of them on
our trip to West Point.

43:17.767 --> 43:20.633 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KATIE MEYLER: But she
stopped in third grade
from going to school
because her family doesn't

43:20.633 --> 43:22.133 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
have any money.

43:22.133 --> 43:24.100 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: What can
you do for a child like this?

43:24.100 --> 43:28.167 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KATIE MEYLER: So, unfortunately,
our school only has 180
spots, and so, at this point,

43:31.200 --> 43:32.867 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
we don't have any space.

43:32.867 --> 43:35.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO:
And her students are
still playing catchup.

43:35.900 --> 43:40.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Ebola shut down all schools
in Liberia for a full year,
a period when educating girls

43:42.900 --> 43:46.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
took a back seat to saving
their lives, she says, even
as she feared for her own.

43:46.100 --> 43:50.367 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KATIE MEYLER: What defines
you the most is what you
do despite your fear.

43:50.367 --> 43:52.433 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And so I was extremely afraid.

43:52.433 --> 43:57.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I had -- I signed my power of
attorney away before I left,
just in case something happened.

43:59.033 --> 44:03.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
There was a real,
legitimate concern that
I might not return home.

44:03.333 --> 44:06.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: She had
to bribe her way into the West
Point neighborhood where most

44:06.800 --> 44:08.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of her students live.

44:08.833 --> 44:13.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It had been quarantined and,
she discovered, had virtually
no health services or equipment.

44:15.400 --> 44:18.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
She raised money to buy
ambulances and medical
supplies and turned her
school into a disaster

44:19.233 --> 44:21.267 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
response center.

44:21.267 --> 44:23.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KATIE MEYLER: Our plan was,
do everything you can to keep
everybody alive, and then

44:23.300 --> 44:26.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
when you can't do anything else,
bring dignity in death, so we
did a lot of that, too, like

44:26.200 --> 44:28.800 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
singing to people, praying
with people while they died.

44:28.800 --> 44:33.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Children that were dying
outside, some of them were just
laying outside of the overflow

44:34.267 --> 44:36.333 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
center.

44:36.333 --> 44:38.367 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The ones inside were actually
worse off, because they were the
dead mixed with the living all

44:38.367 --> 44:39.833 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
there.

44:39.833 --> 44:41.333 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And they could barely
move, barely could speak.

44:41.333 --> 44:43.433 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: How
do you recover from that?

44:43.433 --> 44:45.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KATIE MEYLER: I don't want to
get over this, because we have
to do something to make sure

44:45.300 --> 44:47.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
it doesn't happen again.

44:47.333 --> 44:51.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think that remembering and
feeling what it felt like and
to see that national emergency,

44:53.367 --> 44:57.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
it motivates me and fuels
me to fight to ensure that
it doesn't happen again.

44:57.500 --> 45:01.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Meyler
believes one of the main
contributors to the Ebola crisis

45:01.100 --> 45:05.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
was the lack of education,
so she went to the government
to propose that some private

45:05.500 --> 45:08.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
groups be brought into
overhaul the system.

45:08.433 --> 45:13.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
A pilot project began this
past fall using seven different
organizations to revamp 94

45:16.000 --> 45:17.667 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
schools.

45:17.667 --> 45:20.500 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
More Than Me was put in charge
of six of those schools.

45:20.500 --> 45:25.367 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We met up with Meyler at a
back-to-school celebration in
the rural village of Bogbeh.

45:25.367 --> 45:29.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KATIE MEYLER: Most of the
parents and the community
members here don't read or write

45:29.700 --> 45:31.667 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and didn't have basic education.

45:31.667 --> 45:36.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, they're really excited that
out of 2,750 public schools
in the country that really

45:38.400 --> 45:41.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
aren't functioning, barely
functioning, if functioning
at all, that their school was

45:41.600 --> 45:43.667 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
selected among a few.

45:43.667 --> 45:48.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Meyler and
her staff have helped oversee
school repairs, the development

45:50.000 --> 45:54.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
of new curricula and
installation of teacher
trainers at each
of the six schools.

45:56.067 --> 46:00.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The attention she earned during
the Ebola crisis, including
being named a "TIME" magazine

46:01.533 --> 46:05.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Person of the Year, has opened
the doors to philanthropists.

46:07.000 --> 46:10.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Meyler hopes to raise $25
million over the next five
years to expand to 500 schools.

46:12.367 --> 46:16.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But, ultimately, she hopes
the partnership project is so
successful that the private

46:16.333 --> 46:18.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
partners can
relinquish their roles.

46:18.500 --> 46:20.567 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
KATIE MEYLER: Our goal here
is to go out of business.

46:20.567 --> 46:23.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I mean, I can tell you, for
us, we're successful when
we're not needed anymore.

46:23.700 --> 46:28.467 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We're successful when Liberia's
government can run these
schools, and the teachers are

46:28.467 --> 46:33.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
at capacity, and Liberia
doesn't need to have all
these -- the external support.

46:33.400 --> 46:35.467 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And that's what
we working toward.

46:35.467 --> 46:39.467 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: While she
hopes to go out of business
in a more prosperous future

46:39.467 --> 46:44.467 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Liberia, for her own future,
Meyler says she has no plans
to leave her adopted country.

46:46.067 --> 46:50.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
For the "PBS NewsHour,"
I'm Fred de Sam Lazaro
in Monrovia, Liberia.

46:52.800 --> 46:55.633 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And Fred's
reporting is a partnership
with the Under-Told
Stories Project at the

46:56.800 --> 47:00.967 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
University of St.
Thomas in Minnesota.

47:09.100 --> 47:12.400 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Now to another in our Brief
But Spectacular series.

47:12.400 --> 47:17.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In honor of Black History Month,
we turn to poet Clint Smith,
a doctoral student at Harvard

47:18.433 --> 47:19.633 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
University.

47:19.633 --> 47:21.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
He studies racial
inequality in the U.S.

47:21.633 --> 47:26.467 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And his first full-length
collection of poems, "Counting
Descent," was published in 2016.

47:28.333 --> 47:30.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CLINT SMITH, Harvard University:
A letter to five of the
presidents who owned slaves

47:30.800 --> 47:32.867 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
while they were in office.

47:32.867 --> 47:37.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
George Washington, when you
won the revolution, how many of
your soldiers did you send from

47:37.433 --> 47:39.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
a battlefield to
the cotton field?

47:39.433 --> 47:41.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
How many had to trade in
their rifles for plows?

47:41.533 --> 47:45.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Can you blame the slaves who ran
away to fight for the British,
because at least the Redcoats

47:45.700 --> 47:47.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
were honest about
their oppression?

47:47.833 --> 47:51.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Thomas Jefferson, when
you told Sally Hemings
that you would free her
children if she remained

47:51.200 --> 47:53.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
your mistress, did you
think there was honor
in your ultimatum?

47:53.700 --> 47:56.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Did you think we wouldn't
be able to recognize the
assault in your signature?

47:56.900 --> 48:01.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Does raping your slave, when
you disguise it as bribery,
make it less of a crime?

48:01.433 --> 48:05.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
When you wrote the Declaration
of Independence, did you ever
intend for black people to have

48:05.200 --> 48:07.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
freedom over their
bodies, James Madison?

48:07.433 --> 48:10.667 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
When you wrote to Congress
that black people should count
as three-fifths of a person,

48:10.667 --> 48:14.167 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
how long did you have
to look at your slaves
to figure out the math?

48:14.167 --> 48:15.800 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Was it easy to chop them up?

48:15.800 --> 48:17.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Did you think they would
be happy being more
than just half-human?

48:17.800 --> 48:22.167 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
James Monroe, when you proposed
sending slaves back to Africa,
did black bodies feel like

48:22.167 --> 48:24.200 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
rented tools?

48:24.200 --> 48:27.167 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
When you branded them, did
the scar on their chest
include an expiration date?

48:27.167 --> 48:30.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
When you named the
country Liberia, were
you trying to be ironic?

48:30.433 --> 48:32.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Does this really
count as liberation?

48:32.200 --> 48:35.667 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Andrew Jackson, was the Trail
of Tears not enough for you?

48:35.667 --> 48:40.667 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Was killing Cherokee, Choctaw,
Creek, Seminoles not enough
to quench your imperialism?

48:43.167 --> 48:45.867 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
How many brown bodies
do you have to bulldoze
before you can call it
progress, Mr. Washington,

48:47.000 --> 48:49.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Jefferson, Madison,
Monroe, Jackson?

48:49.033 --> 48:52.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
When you put your hand on the
Bible and swore to protect this
country, let's be honest in

48:52.533 --> 48:54.567 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
who you were talking about.

48:54.567 --> 48:57.967 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
When the first Independence
Day fireworks set the sky
aflame, don't forget where we

48:57.967 --> 49:00.567 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
were watching from.

49:00.567 --> 49:02.967 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, when you remember
Jefferson's genius, don't
forget the slaves who
built the bookshelves

49:02.967 --> 49:05.500 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in his library.

49:05.500 --> 49:08.433 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
When you remember
Jackson's victories in
war, don't forget what he
was fighting to preserve.

49:08.433 --> 49:12.467 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
When you sing that this country
was founded on freedom, don't
forget the duet of shackles

49:12.467 --> 49:15.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
dragging against the
ground my entire life.

49:15.300 --> 49:20.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I have been taught how perfect
this country was, but no one
ever told me about the pages

49:20.233 --> 49:24.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
torn out of my textbooks, how
black and brown bodies have been
bludgeoned for three centuries

49:24.500 --> 49:27.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
and find no place
in the curriculum.

49:27.833 --> 49:31.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Oppression doesn't disappear
just because you decided not
to teach us that chapter.

49:31.700 --> 49:36.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
If you only hear one side of
the story, at some point, you
have to question who the writer

49:37.267 --> 49:39.900 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
is.

49:39.900 --> 49:44.900 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I'm a third-year graduate
student at Harvard University.

49:49.500 --> 49:53.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I study broadly the
history of racial inequality
in the United States.

49:53.100 --> 49:56.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I taught high school English
for several years in Prince
George's County, Maryland.

49:56.833 --> 50:00.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And part of what I always
think about is how important
it is to complicate history.

50:00.800 --> 50:05.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The presidents and the founding
fathers and all of the people
we sort of raise up as false

50:07.867 --> 50:09.867 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
idols, we don't wrestle with
the fact that many of these
were brilliant men, but they

50:09.867 --> 50:14.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
were also men with
deep prejudices against
people of color, against
indigenous people,

50:14.433 --> 50:17.000 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
against women.

50:17.000 --> 50:19.600 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Jefferson I learned
about was the intellectual
founding father of this
country, responsible

50:19.600 --> 50:23.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
for the conception of the
Declaration of Independence
and the Constitution.

50:23.100 --> 50:26.100 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And we never talked about the
fact that he owned slaves.

50:26.100 --> 50:30.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Only after we understand
where we have come from can we
understand how we need to move

50:30.100 --> 50:31.100 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
forward.

50:31.100 --> 50:33.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
My name is Clint Smith.

50:33.000 --> 50:36.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And this is my Brief But
Spectacular take on complicating
the history of the United

50:36.133 --> 50:38.100 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
States.

50:38.100 --> 50:41.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And you can
find additional Brief But
Spectacular episodes on our Web

50:41.533 --> 50:46.533 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
site, PBS.org/NewsHour/Brief.

50:47.433 --> 50:49.867 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And now to a "NewsHour" Shares.

50:49.867 --> 50:53.400 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In 2006, after billionaire
businessman Warren
Buffett announced that
he was giving away

50:53.400 --> 50:57.467 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
much of his fortune,
people started writing him
letters asking for help.

50:57.467 --> 51:01.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He turned them over to his
sister, who has been responding
to them ever since as part

51:01.633 --> 51:03.133 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of a foundation.

51:03.133 --> 51:07.867 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Tina Martin from PBS station
WGBH in Boston has the story.

51:09.900 --> 51:13.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TINA MARTIN: These letters are
from people from all across
the country who are desperate

51:13.933 --> 51:16.433 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
for help.

51:16.433 --> 51:19.933 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NONI CAMPBELL, Letters
Foundation: Somebody would
say, I'm on disability
and I need dentures

51:20.800 --> 51:22.500 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and I don't have any money.

51:22.500 --> 51:23.733 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Could you help me with dentures?

51:23.733 --> 51:25.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
TINA MARTIN: Some
are handwritten.

51:25.100 --> 51:27.167 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Others are typed.

51:27.167 --> 51:31.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But they all come to the Letters
Foundation, run by billionaire
Warren Buffet's older sister,

51:32.100 --> 51:34.133 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Doris.

51:34.133 --> 51:36.867 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
She started reading letters
at the request of her brother,
who was being flooded with

51:36.867 --> 51:41.200 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
pleas for help.

51:41.200 --> 51:45.667 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Noni Campbell is a
longtime friend of Doris,
lovingly called Dodo.

51:45.667 --> 51:47.733 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
They met more than a decade ago.

51:47.733 --> 51:52.167 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
NONI CAMPBELL: She had a blue
sofa in her condo up in Maine,
and she would be sitting

51:54.133 --> 51:57.067 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in one little corner of it,
and the entire rest of the sofa
was piled with letters from

51:57.067 --> 51:59.167 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
people, boxes and boxes.

51:59.167 --> 52:02.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TINA MARTIN: All of those
boxes came with Doris Buffett
when she moved to Boston, but

52:02.300 --> 52:07.300 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
she needed help reading them;
1,200 people volunteered.

52:10.267 --> 52:12.400 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Emily Holland was one of them.

52:12.400 --> 52:14.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
EMILY HOLLAND, Letters
Foundation: I think we
don't want to believe
how easy it is to

52:14.500 --> 52:19.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
fall into a situation that's
overwhelming or that we feel
like we can't get out of.

52:21.067 --> 52:25.467 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TINA MARTIN: Volunteers are
being trained over the next
several weeks, but not everyone

52:26.200 --> 52:28.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
will read letters,

52:28.200 --> 52:30.267 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
AMY KINGMAN, Letters Foundation:
We actually created a new
role, which are the group -- a

52:30.267 --> 52:33.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
number of people who are
here training today, and
those are our researchers.

52:33.400 --> 52:37.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TINA MARTIN: The researchers
will verify people's
identities and stories.

52:37.300 --> 52:42.300 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They also make sure requests
fulfill the foundation's
mission of making
one-time grants to help

52:43.167 --> 52:44.800 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
them get back on their feet.

52:44.800 --> 52:47.067 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Unfortunately,
businesses is brisk.

52:47.067 --> 52:49.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
TEVIS SPEZIA, Letters
Foundation: Since we
have been in Boston,
we have given out about

52:49.833 --> 52:53.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
260,000 in the
fiscal year of 2016.

52:53.500 --> 52:58.467 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
In total, we have given out
about a little over 300,000 now.

52:58.467 --> 53:03.467 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We give any sorts of grants
upwards of $35,000 in a case
like that that's a handicap van,

53:05.500 --> 53:10.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and you have to spend a little
bit more to provide the vehicle,
and then smaller amounts

53:10.300 --> 53:14.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to cover some utilities and
help people get back on their
feet can be as small as $200,

53:14.800 --> 53:16.867 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
$300.

53:16.867 --> 53:20.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
TINA MARTIN: While the
foundation operates
with a strict budget,
there is no budget when

53:20.000 --> 53:22.067 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
it comes to giving.

53:22.067 --> 53:24.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TEVIS SPEZIA: If anyone has
worked closely with Doris, she
always speaks about how she

53:24.333 --> 53:25.767 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
wants her last check to bounce.

53:25.767 --> 53:28.867 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
TINA MARTIN: The Buffett
family is also very hands-on.

53:28.867 --> 53:33.867 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Now 89, Doris isn't
always in the office, but
talks with staff daily.

53:35.733 --> 53:38.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's part of her personal
touch, like how people are
required to make a request with

53:38.500 --> 53:40.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
old-fashioned letters.

53:40.533 --> 53:43.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MIMI ROZEK, Letters Foundation:
She really loves the personal
connection of a handwritten

53:43.400 --> 53:45.467 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
letter.

53:45.467 --> 53:47.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That's how the program really
started, too, with Warren,
was people writing and sending

53:47.433 --> 53:49.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
in physical letters.

53:49.433 --> 53:53.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TINA MARTIN: And Mimi Rozek,
Doris' granddaughter, promises
they read every letter.

53:53.100 --> 53:55.233 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
MIMI ROZEK: It's very humbling.

53:55.233 --> 53:58.767 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And, at times, it's a little
bit stressful, just because
sometimes we can't help with

53:58.767 --> 54:02.267 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
all of them for various
reasons, but the vast
majority, we are able to help.

54:02.267 --> 54:03.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And that's really great.

54:03.933 --> 54:06.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
TINA MARTIN: For the
"PBS NewsHour," I'm
Tina Martin in Boston.

54:06.933 --> 54:08.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: That's
an inspiration.

54:08.900 --> 54:10.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And that's the
"NewsHour" for tonight.

54:10.333 --> 54:12.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm Judy Woodruff.

54:12.400 --> 54:14.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For all of us at the "PBS
NewsHour," thank you,
